title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Share of the rural population, with a total of 13 data points.
Overall Share of the rural population has decreased over the Year.
Share of the rural population is slightly decreasing from 2006 to 2018.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2014 and 2015.
Max Share of the rural population about 22.6 was recorded at Year 2006
Min Share of the rural population about 19.5 was recorded at Year 2018
